subject: p11474065
History: History: F with sob hx tracheobronchomalasia, aacute process.
Findings: Compared the prior study, there is increase in opacity at the right mid to lower lung difficult to exclude small left pleural effusion. Pneumonia pneumothorax is seen. The cardiac and mediastinal silhouettes are stable. Chronic deformity of the posterior right fourth rib.
Impression: Increase in opacity at the right mid to lower lung is nonspecific, could be due to infection and/ or aspiration.
